keyValuePair.Value: A bitter pill to swallow. Did you deserve to go out, though?
It was such a tight affair, I'm sure you're very disappointed this defeat sees you go out. But did your team do enough over the two legs?
We made mistakes at the wrong times.

In this competition every mistake can potentially cost you a place in the next round. The lads know only too well that they lost focus at the wrong times today. And that's why we're out, I'm afraid. It's a blow.
We have to go again for the fans.

After the draw in the first leg, I'm sure our supporters expected to be celebrating today. But we came up short. It's frustrating. A little more luck on our side and we could have been the team going through. It was that close. Now, we'll have to go again. We owe it to those fans.
Perhaps I need to take some blame here.

I have to be honest with myself. Maybe I was too conservative in setting up the team. I didn't give the lads enough the freedom to go forward and we spent too much time on the back foot. I'm very sorry we're out of the %1s. We all have to learn from this. Me included.
Close. But no cigar. Where did you come up short today?
It was a very tight tie between two good teams, but %1s are celebrating the win and a place in the semis and your boys are out. In hindsight, could you have done anything differently?
It was just one of those days for us.

We competed well across the two games. The boys put in a lot of hard graft for very little reward. It probably came down to the luck not really going our way in either leg. I can't fault any of my players for effort, that's for sure.
Winners celebrate. Losers make their own arrangements.
It's very tough on the players. I think they played well in both games and this one could have gone either way. It wasn't to be but we'll pick ourselves up and be better for the experience.
We just didn't do enough going forward.

The games were close and there were plenty of things my team did well. But it all came down to finding that bit of quality to turn the tie one way or the other. We probably didn't do enough going forward. The opposition made a couple of chances and took them. That's why we're out of the %1s, simple as that.
How frustrating is it to miss out on the Final?
There was so little to choose between the two teams across the two legs. Football can be a pretty cruel game. Can your team's confidence re3cover from that?
We owe our fans more.

We had a job to do here and we've not been quite good enough. Our fans have been amazing throughout the competition. I'm desperately disappointed that we couldn't reward them with a place in the Final. We owe it to them now to be better in future.
It could have gone either way.
I can't say that I'm happy, but we did our best so I can't fault the players.

The boys can be proud of having taken %1s to the brink of a Final. But luck wasn't with us today and a couple of bad bounces have cost us at key moments. I just hope things will go our way next time we're in this sort of position.

The boys can be proud of having taken %1s to the brink of a Final. But luck wasn't with us today and a couple of bad bounces have cost us at key moments. I just hope things will go our way next time we're in this sort of position.
We've missed our big chance today.

We were so close to something special here. I really think we've missed a great chance of reaching the Final and maybe even lifting the trophy. It's frustrating. A little more aggression and a bit more self-belief and things could have been so different!

We were so close to something special here. I really think we've missed a great chance of reaching the Final and maybe even lifting the trophy. It's frustrating. A little more aggression and a bit more self-belief and things could have been so different!
It was a narrow defeat but what went wrong for you today?
It was close. Another goal and you'd have made it through. What could your %1s team have done better today? Where did you miss out?
We shouldn't have conceded when we did.

Yes, another goal would have taken us through. But why were we in that position? If the boys had been switched on and been better organised earlier in today's game, it need' t have come down to us chasing things late on.
I'll look at the game back and then pass judgement.

Two close games and it's hard to tell, really, what the difference was between the two sides. I'll look back at what happened and take my time working out how to make sure we're better prepared in the future.
The lads worked hard enough, for sure.

It's disappointing not to progress but I can't fault the boys for effort. They ran themselves into the ground, didn't they. A lucky bounce for us in a key moment for us and it could have been a very different outcome.
